<br>
Couple groups come in to do reavers and lords.  I think to myself... no problem... we can pull to the stables and stay out of their way.  Raiders decide to pull to the bridge.  Still I am not too worried.  They have enough people of the right levels and classes to control their mobs.  We settle in and start hunting.  Blam... someone from raid takes wrong turn and we get slammed by train.  (Yeah, I know you shouted that you were taking something to the zone but hey bud, the zone is the other way.  Get a map next time or ask if someone is there before taking a detour.)<br>
<br>
LOADING...PLEASE WAIT<br>
You lose a level!<br>
<br>
Crap, now I am back in hell again.  I look around to see almost all of the rest of my group standing there naked (I would have enjoyed the scenery more had I been alive.)  Only one cleric was able to gate out.  I get rezzed and regain my level (thank the gods for clerics).  Ranger and warrior get rezzed and bail on us.  Due to some wacky bug, other cleric's body got stuck in floor and can't be pulled or rezzed.  We beg repeatedly for the zone group and raiders to please stop pulling for one minute so we can get her back to corpse.  After several tells, I finally manage to get in touch with the puller from zone group and convince him to stop stacking.  No word from the GM yet so she loots her corpse and takes experience loss.  <br>
<br>
We spend another half hour getting a couple more tanks and set up camp again.  This time we hug the corner as much as we can and stop pulling from near temple.  Again another train rushes by (this time with no warning) and six cars jump the tracks to attack tank who is chasing dying golem that just broke root.  The group is LOM so I order them to ZONE!  I look over my shoulder and see nobody following me.  Damn lag!  I shout ZONE!!! RUN!!! NOW!!! (more exclamation points usually get more attention.)  Tanks still ignore me but my friends start to follow me.  I stop to root a few skels, canni, and pour the rest of my mana into the one most injured then book it to safety.  Half of the group dies but this time we are able to drag them to the zone for rezzes despite the fact that rogue abandoned us sometime during the combat without a word.  Freaking coward!<br>
<br>
We snatch up rogue that just zoned in and head back to spot.  Fifteen minutes later... just as we had gotten into routine, big ass train including bunch of goos heads out of the station.  Somewhat gun shy now, we run for zone.  There is such a crowd of people from raid there that I can't get out.  I ask politely if they can step aside so I can zone.  Nobody does.  I try to jump over them or duck around them but that doesn’t work.  I repeat my request a little more urgently since I really don't want to be first one in the hallway to get slammed by the train.  Nobody listens.  I repeat in CAPITAL LETTERS.  One person moves a few inches.  I realize that I will never be able to push my way through in time so I tell the others (all skinny little elves) to leave me and start to mem gate.  Cars roll in and I get hit by goo before I can finish.  Root gets resisted but topors and poison doesn't.  It aggros on me.  I try to move to the right... ogres.  I try to move to the left... trolls.  Trapped in the corner now, I yell for help.<br>
<br>
LOADING...PLEASE WAIT<br>
You lose a level!<br>
<br>
Quite pissed now but determined not to lose my temper because I can probably get level back with another rez, I sit down and open up my spellbook.  One person who just ignored my cries for help asks me for SoW and some buffs.  Another who had blocked my escape asks me for a heal and SoW.  (WTF! Why should I even lift a finger for you? I just got killed while both of you stood there and watched me die.  Plz, you tell me. Without a word, I stand up and give you what you asked for. Thx, you say. Yeah, right... now leave me alone... I have another rez incoming, warrior just camped on us, and GM finally showed up.)<br>
<br>
Arrggghhhh!<br>
<br>
